Pre-processing¶

In [6]:
## As I have known cases_roc and deaths_roc have extreme values
dat= dat[(dat["cases_roc"]< dat["cases_roc"].quantile(0.99)) & (dat["cases_roc"]> dat["cases_roc"].quantile(0.01))]
In [7]:
## Convert to int for analysis
dat["cases_roc"]= [int(i) for i in dat["cases_roc"]]
dat["deaths_roc"]= [int(i) for i in dat["deaths_roc"]]
dat["cases_worse"]= np.where(dat["cases_roc"]> dat["cases_roc"].mean(),1,0)
In [8]:

                'week_end', 'date_start', 'date_end', 'target_country', 'compliance'])

Initialize the Pipeline¶

In [11]:
## Set the folds index to ensure comparable samples
fold_generator = KFold(n_splits=10, shuffle=True,random_state=1234)

## Initalize the pipe
pipe = Pipeline(steps=[('pre_process', pp.MinMaxScaler()),('model',None)])

search_space = [
    # Naive Bayes
    {'model': [NB()]},

    # KNN with K tuning param
    {'model' : [KNN()],
     'model__n_neighbors':[5,10,25,50]},

    # Decision Tree with the Max Depth Param
    {'model': [DT()],
     'model__max_depth':[2,3,4]},

    # Random forest with the N Estimators tuning param
    {'model' : [RF()],
    'model__max_depth':[2,3,4],
    'model__n_estimators':[500,1000,1500]}

]

search = GridSearchCV(pipe, search_space,
                      cv = fold_generator,
                      scoring='roc_auc',
                      n_jobs=4)
In [12]:
## Search the best fit 
search.fit(train_X,train_y)

Permutation Importance¶

In [17]:
## Get permutation importance with 25 repeating times
vi = permutation_importance(rf_mod,train_X,train_y,n_repeats=25)

## Organize as a data frame
vi_dat = pd.DataFrame(dict(variable=train_X.columns,
                           vi = vi['importances_mean'],
                           std = vi['importances_std']))

## Generate intervals
vi_dat['low'] = vi_dat['vi'] - 2*vi_dat['std']
vi_dat['high'] = vi_dat['vi'] + 2*vi_dat['std']

## take the order from the most to least important
vi_dat = vi_dat.sort_values(by="vi",ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
In [20]:
## Plot PI 
cases_auc_roc= (ggplot(vi_dat, aes(x="variable",y="vi")) +
    geom_col(alpha=.5) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin="low",ymax="high"),width=.2) +
    theme_bw() +
    scale_x_discrete(limits=vi_dat.variable.tolist()) +
    coord_flip() +
    labs(y="Reduction in AUC ROC",x=""))

ICE Plots¶

In [23]:
def gen_ice_plot(var_name = None):
    pdp_dist = pdp.pdp_isolate(model = rf_mod, 
                               dataset = train_X,
                               model_features = train_X.columns.tolist(),
                               feature=var_name)

    fig,ax = pdp.pdp_plot(pdp_dist,var_name,plot_pts_dist=True,plot_lines=True)

gen_ice_plot(var_name= "week_start")
